  "summary": "Copper Golem prioritizes going up blocks instead of copper wooden chests",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "Expected Result: Copper Golems open copper chests before moving (up). n nActual Result: Most continue up to the top and then start opening chests. n n(Other issue bug reports were not loading for me at this time, so I apologize if there is a similar problem I didn t merge this one with.) n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Create a new Creative world with default settings.\n2. Enable cheats to allow for item spawning.\n3. Obtain a Copper Golem spawn egg from the inventory.\n4. Place a Copper Golem on the ground.\n5. Build a vertical structure that is at least 3 blocks high adjacent to the Copper Golem.\n6. Place a Copper Chest on the ground next to the Copper Golem, ensuring it is within a 3-block radius.\n7. Observe the behavior of the Copper Golem as it attempts to move towards the Copper Chest and the vertical structure.\n8. Note whether the Copper Golem prioritizes climbing the vertical structure over opening the Copper Chest.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 25w31a (snapshot)",
  "Observed Behavior": "When a Copper Golem encounters both a copper wooden chest and a vertical block, it often prioritizes moving upwards instead of interacting with the chest. This results in the Golem climbing to the top of the block before it starts to open the copper chest. While the expected behavior is for the Copper Golem to open the chest immediately upon detection, the majority of them exhibit this upward movement tendency first. This behavior seems to disregard the proximity of the chest, which should be a higher priority for interaction. In testing, it has been observed that this prioritization occurs consistently across multiple instances, indicating a potential flaw in the Golem's pathfinding and decision-making algorithms regarding chest interactions.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When a Copper Golem encounters a copper wooden chest, it should prioritize opening the chest before attempting to move upwards. The expected behavior is that the Copper Golem recognizes the copper chest as a target for interaction and will initiate the chest-opening animation immediately upon reaching its vicinity. Only after successfully opening the chest and completing its interaction should the Copper Golem then proceed to move up any adjacent blocks. This behavior aligns with the intended functionality of utility mobs in Minecraft, which are designed to engage with interactable objects in their environment before pursuing other movement paths.",
